From: doujialong <doujialong@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH] ARM: dts: sun8i-h3: nanopi-m1-plus: fix RGMII PHY mode

The NanoPi M1 Plus uses a Realtek RTL8211E RGMII PHY. With the upstream
DTS using plain "rgmii" phy-mode, neither the MAC nor the PHY inserts
the clock delay required by RGMII, which results in a link coming up
(LEDs on) but no traffic being able to pass in either direction.

Change phy-mode to "rgmii-id" so that the PHY inserts the internal RX
and TX clock delays. This matches what other H3 boards using the same
external RTL8211E PHY (e.g. NanoPi K1 Plus, OrangePi Plus 2E) do and
restores working ethernet on NanoPi M1 Plus.

Reported-by: doujialong
Signed-off-by: doujialong <doujialong@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 arch/arm/boot/dts/sun8i-h3-nanopi-m1-plus.dts | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/sun8i-h3-nanopi-m1-plus.dts
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/sun8i-h3-nanopi-m1-plus.dts
@@ -90,7 +90,7 @@
 	pinctrl-0 = <&emac_rgmii_pins>;
 	phy-supply = <&reg_gmac_3v3>;
 	phy-handle = <&ext_rgmii_phy>;
-	phy-mode = "rgmii";
+	phy-mode = "rgmii-id";
 
 	status = "okay";
 };
